# docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-01-nelix-hook-state-detection-design.md §1 and the sibling capture
# tests/test_bg_subagent_realcapture.py (session s-039a61b4: a `golang-pro` BACKGROUND subagent ran for
# ~8 min while the daemon flapped publish:waiting_for_user / withdraw:prompt_changed ~35x — the SCREEN
# showed a live `❯` box + a "Waiting for N background agent(s) to finish" line, misread as free_text).
# No LIVE hook recording was available to the author, so each payload is hand-authored to the real
# Claude hook shape in the true turn order:
#   UserPromptSubmit -> PreToolUse[Task] (spawn subagent) -> many PreToolUse/PostToolUse (main agent +
#   subagent tool work) -> PostToolUse[Task] (subagent finished) -> Stop (only NOW -> idle).
# The whole point: NO Stop and NO AskUserQuestion fire mid-flight, so the state stays `busy` for every
# event until the final Stop. Locks out the bg-subagent flap by construction.
